[Authors] Dudu and Lele

[Need] [Winch] Yes

[To] Noxdar Darmeth

[NPC Internal] You look like you could use some help.
[NPC] Noxdar: Oh, hello.
[NPC] Noxdar: You wanted to do something for me?
[NPC] Noxdar: Yes, I suppose you could.
[NPC] Noxdar: I'm having a little difficulty with the affairs of the heart.
[NPC] Noxdar: Still want to get involved?
[NPC Internal] I'd not like it to be said that I'm all fight and no heart. I'll help.
[NPC] Noxdar: Thanks.
[NPC] Noxdar: I've been seeing Frilaa Bhundri, an enkidukai in the Plaza area, for a little while now.
[NPC] Noxdar: However, I discovered something shocking: she is married and did not tell me!
[NPC] Noxdar: Please, if you could, tell her that I must stop courtship.
[NPC] Noxdar: She will no doubt ask why I do so, and why I do not go myself.
[NPC Narrate] -Noxdar coughs nervously.-
[NPC] Noxdar: Just tell her I'm busy with work.
[NPC] Noxdar: Whatever you do, do not let on that I know she's married!
[NPC] Noxdar: There are things at stake which you do not know about!
[NPC Narrate] -Noxdar begins sweating.-
[NPC] Noxdar: I wish you well, and I hope you do the right thing.

[To] Frilaa Bhundri

[NPC Internal] Noxdar is saddened to inform you that he must cease his courtship of you.
[NPC] Frilaa: You did not just tell me that Noxdar sent someone in his place to break it off with me!
[NPC Narrate] -Frilaa makes a snapping noise with her paw.-
[NPC] Frilaa: I don't suppose he gave you a reason?
[NPC Internal] Work steals his every waking moment.
[NPC] Frilaa: I…I see.
[NPC] Frilaa: That is unfortunate.
[NPC] Frilaa: I know he's been trying to be an engineer; I didn't realize how time-consuming it could be.
[NPC Narrate] -Frilaa ponders the situation.-
[NPC] Frilaa: Wait, does he know about my husband?

[Possible Ways] 2

[Way] 1

[NPC Internal] Husband? I don't know what you're talking about.
[NPC] Frilaa: He doesn't?
[NPC] Frilaa: That's good.
[NPC] Frilaa: If he did, he'd have to duel with my husband sooner or later.
[NPC] Frilaa: But this break-up is for the best.
[NPC] Frilaa: Here, give him this letter.
[NPC Narrate] -Frilaa pulls out a paper and pen, and hastily writes a sweet letter. She then hands it to you.-
[NPC] Frilaa: Please give that to Noxdar Darmeth.

[To] Noxdar Darmeth

[NPC Internal] Here, she wrote you a letter.
[NPC] Noxdar: A letter from Frilaa, for me?
